This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on domain adaptation for sequence labeling, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of hidden Markov models (HMMs) is a common technique in machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes using HMMs to learn word representations, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the influence of using data from different domains, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the domains are image-based.
